Add a StringLiteral class as a replacement for JavaWriter.StringLiteral.  Advantages include:   * References differentiate between String and StringLiteral   * StringLiteral.toString() still allows to be directly passed to String.format, et. al.   * You can get the value back after the literal has been passed around.
